tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, indicating impaired renal function, and mildly elevated ALT, suggesting possible mild liver involvement or injury. All other parameters, including glucose, electrolytes, proteins, and lipid profile, are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation and further evaluation of renal and liver function.
